==English==

===Verb===
{{en-verb|inf=[[bring]] [[down]]|brings down|bringing down|brought down}}

# To make a [[legitimate]] [[rulership]] lose their position of power.
#: ''The rebel forces are trying to '''bring down''' the president and his government.''
# To [[reduce]]
#: The latest budget reforms are intended to '''bring down''' the level of inflation.''
# To make something flying fall to the ground. Usually by firing a [[weapon]] of some kind.
#: ''He '''brought down''' a pheasant with his first shot of the day.''
# To make someone feel bad [[emotionally]].
#: The news of his death '''brought''' her '''down'''.


====Synonyms====
* make something flying fall to the ground: shoot down
* make someone feel bad [[emotionally]]: harsh one's mellow
* make a [[legitimate]] [[rulership]] lose their position of power: overthrow 

====See also====
* [[bring down the house]]

====Usage notes====
The object may appear before or after the particle. If the object is a pronoun, then it must be before the particle.

